<h3>What is RSS?</h3>
<p>RSS is a family of web feed formats used to publish frequently updated content. RSS allows people to keep current with their favorite websites without having to visit them repeatedly. Content from RSS feeds can be read using special software generally called "RSS readers" or "feed readers".  These readers are commonly now found as part of web browsers including Firefox.
</p>
<h3>What is a Podcast?</h3>
<p>A podcast is media, such as video or audio, distributed via RSS.  Often people subscribe to podcasts through applications such as iTunes.
For instructions on how to subscribe to podcasts via Itunes, click the following : 
<a href='http://www.apple.com/support/itunes/store/podcast/'>http://www.apple.com/support/itunes/store/podcast/ </a>
</p>